headline: Wells Fargo joins Wall Street chorus in lifting S&P 500's annual target
summary: The Wells Fargo bank subsidiary sees the benchmark index ending 2025 between 6,300 and 6,500, up from a prior range of 5,900 to 6,100.  The target raise follows U.S. President Donald Trump delaying his reciprocal tariffs and signing deals with trade partners including EU and Japan.  Earlier this month, Trump also signed into law tax and spending cuts that would benefit corporate earnings.
